Reasoning: 
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the geometric representation of graphs and their properties.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper discusses the complexity of drawing graphs with few bends per edge.
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is relevant as the paper deals with planar graphs and their properties.
- cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) is relevant as the paper discusses the properties of graphs and their representation, which can be applied to game theory.
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with graph representation, which can be applied to social networks.
